From: Chris Wilcox <chris.wilcox@consensys.net>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 13:17:28 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] test: skip flaky mUSD Conversion Happy Path E2E spec

The wallet-platform-android-smoke-2 shard has been intermittently
failing on main and on unrelated PRs since #29247 ("ci: reuse native
E2E builds across commits and PRs"). Multiple it() blocks inside
musd-conversion-happy-path.spec.ts have been observed failing across
different runs, so the entire describe is skipped as an unblock.

Re-enablement is tracked under MMQA-1812.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 tests/smoke/wallet/musd-conversion-happy-path.spec.ts | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tests/smoke/wallet/musd-conversion-happy-path.spec.ts b/tests/smoke/wallet/musd-conversion-happy-path.spec.ts
index 2c601717..2a4a3a32 100644
--- a/tests/smoke/wallet/musd-conversion-happy-path.spec.ts
+++ b/tests/smoke/wallet/musd-conversion-happy-path.spec.ts
@@ -52,7 +52,10 @@ function withMusdFixturesOptions(
   };
 }
 
-describe(SmokeWalletPlatform('mUSD Conversion Happy Path'), () => {
+// TODO(MMQA-1812): Re-enable once the wallet-platform-android-smoke-2 flakiness is resolved.
+// Multiple it() blocks in this spec have been observed failing on different runs since
+// the E2E build-reuse change in #29247. Tracking via MMQA-1812.
+describe.skip(SmokeWalletPlatform('mUSD Conversion Happy Path'), () => {
   beforeAll(async () => {
     jest.setTimeout(150000);
     // Do not launch app here: launch happens inside withFixtures (restartDevice: true)
-- 
